 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-EXT TYPE-DEFECTS (from AUDIT_REPORT Section 4.4): 7 type system defects. (1) Value::Keyword accepts unvalidated String — 392 call sites construct Value::Keyword with no format check. Should validate :keyword format. (2) EntityId::ZERO sentinel violates C2 — not content-derived, use Option<EntityId> instead. (3) TxId has public fields bypassing HLC — direct construction bypasses tick()/merge() monotonicity guarantees. (4) SpecId stores element_type as bare String — should be enum {Inv, Adr, Neg} with private fields. (5) SchemaError::Inconsistency is catch-all — single String variant for all schema violations, not caller-distinguishable. (6) Bare String for TaskId, ShardId, etc. — missing newtypes for structurally constrained strings. (7) Attribute cloning in hot paths — 131 clone() calls in store.rs for ~200 unique attributes that should be interned. JUSTIFICATION: Each excess cardinality (|Type| > |ValidStates|) is a runtime error waiting to happen. The type system should make invalid states unrepresentable. TxId with public fields is the most concerning — it allows construction of causally-incoherent timestamps, bypassing the HLC guarantees. SOLUTION: (1) Add Keyword validation at construction. (2) Replace EntityId::ZERO with Option<EntityId>. (3) Make TxId fields private with constructors. (4) Make SpecId use an enum. (5) Expand SchemaError variants. (6) Add newtypes. (7) Intern attributes. VERIFICATION: For each: attempting invalid construction fails at compile time or returns Err. DEPENDENCIES: (7) overlaps with AUDIT-EXT-PERF-MEMORY. (4) overlaps with F-C8 (SpecId is DDIS-specific). FILES: datom.rs, spec_id.rs, error.rs, store.rs. SEVERITY: P2-P3. WAVE: 1-2. EFFORT: 8h total."
